I've attached the online description below from Sweetwater music. The Warmth of a solid rosewood back and sides body in an Acoustic/Electric Jumbo! Epiphone revives the prestige of its 1930s guitars with the new Masterbilt Acoustic Series. These new flat-top guitars feature solid wood construction and a distinctive 1930s-style "offset notch" peghead shape with historic Epiphone script logo and mother-of-pearl "stickpin" inlay. The classic Jumbo shape of the AJ-500RE is the preferred guitar of modern music legends. With gracefully sloping shoulders, solid back and sides, and a solid Sitka spruce top, the AJ-500RE blankets a room with deep, rich and rounded tones. The AJ-500RE includes the original Masterbilt pickup system.. The beautiful grain of the Masterbilt woods is enhanced with a natural satin. The dreadnought and fingerstyle models have full-body abalone binding, tapered dovetail neck joints glued with hot hide glue.
